TITLE: COP27: delegates weigh ‘climate compensation' for poor nations impacted by global warming
SUMMARY: Delegates from more than 200 nations at the COP27 climate change conference will discuss sending poor nations compensation for climate change damage.

TITLE: Arkansas Sen. Tom Cotton not running for president in 2024
SUMMARY: Republican Sen. Tom Cotton of Arkansas, a rising star in the GOP, has decided against seeking the presidency in the 2024 election cycle

TITLE: Democrats call in the cavalry trying to save blue seat in key Senate battleground
SUMMARY: Sen. Amy Klobuchar of Minnesota joined her Democratic colleague Sen. Maggie Hassan in New Hampshire two days before Election Day to urge supporters "to turn out the vote."

TITLE: New York governor: Lee Zeldin supporter attacked at rally for Gov. Kathy Hochul, video shows
SUMMARY: A female supporter of GOP gubernatorial candidate Lee Zeldin says she was attacked and assaulted at a rally for Democratic Gov. Kathy Hochul in New York City on Saturday.

TITLE: GOP could win key Florida county for the first time in two decades
SUMMARY: Republicans are threatening to win Florida's typicall blue Miami-Dade County, which has not voted for a Republican candidate for governor since Jeb Bush two decades ago.

TITLE: Dem poll worker ejected for pre-selecting 'straight Dem ticket' on voting machine, calling Rs 'racist'
SUMMARY: Indiana elections officials ejected Democrat poll worker James Zheng for allegedly filling out a ballot and urging voters not to cast ballots for certain candidates.

TITLE: Clyburn doubles down on Nazi Germany comparison, but does sharp about-face on ‘end of the world’ remark
SUMMARY: House Majority Whip Rep. James Clyburn on Sunday doubled down on his claim that the U.S. is headed on the same path as Germany before Adolph Hitler rose to power.

TITLE: Biden's condemnation of violent rhetoric on the right ignores these incendiary comments from his own party
SUMMARY: Democrats have charged right-wing rhetoric was behind the attack on Paul Pelosi. There've been at least 7 instances of Democrats making comments that were accused of being violent.

TITLE: Biden adviser blames COVID-19 for Democrats' difficulty in drawing enthusiam for their messages
SUMMARY: White House adviser Keisha Lance Bottoms pointed to the COVID-19 pandemic in explaining why Democrats have had trouble communicating their messages to the public.

TITLE: Trump to hold midterm rally in Florida, but rival ‘Ron DeSanctimonious’ won’t be there
SUMMARY: Gov. Ron DeSantis was not invited and nor did he ask for an invitation to former President Donald Trump's rally for Sen. Marco Rubio in Florida, reports say.

TITLE: Georgia senate candidate Herschel Walker touts business record, says Warnock 'never built anything'
SUMMARY: Herschel Walker, Georgia's Republican candidate for U.S. senate, boasted his businesssuccess and said incumbent Sen. Raphael Warnock has "never built anything."

TITLE: Dems close October's 9 point enthusiasm gap just days before midterm elections: Poll
SUMMARY: Democrats are closing in on Republicans on measures of enthusiasm just days before the midterm elections, closing a nine point gap over the last month in one poll.

TITLE: Arizona candidate Kari Lake campaign HQ receives 'suspicious items' in mail, prompting Phoenix police response
SUMMARY: Phoenix police confirmed that officers responded after "suspicious items" were found inside the mail at Arizona Republican candidate for governor Kari Lake's campaign headquarters.

TITLE: Sen. Mike Lee says FBI facing 'possible restructuring' to drive out politics from headquarters
SUMMARY: Sen. Mike Lee said the FBI could be hit with restructuring if Republicans take control of Congress. Possible changes would come after hearings led by a GOP majority.

TITLE: RNC wont pay Trump's legal bills if he launches another White House bid, chair says
SUMMARY: Republican National Committee Chairwoman Ronna McDaniel said her organization would no longer pay former President Donald Trump's legal bills if he launched a 2024 campaign.

TITLE: Fetterman, Braddock and a tale of two businesses: How the former mayor impacted the Pittsburgh borough
SUMMARY: Two business leaders in Braddock, Pennsylvania, weighed in on Lt. Gov. John Fetterman's effectiveness during his tenure as the Pittsburgh suburb's mayor.

TITLE: Reliable blocs Dems count on didn’t turn out in Texas early voting
SUMMARY: Texas early voting in the Greater Houston Area was down 7-10%, while key demographics that Democrats typically rely on showed the steepest decline compared to 2018.

TITLE: Rick Scott won’t say whether he’ll support Trump 2024 presidential run
SUMMARY: NRSC Chairman Sen. Rick Scott, R-Fla., wouldn't say on NBC News’ "Meet the Press" whether he would support a third presidential run by former President Donald Trump.

TITLE: Pompeo runs to DeSantis' defense after Trump lands first blow with new nickname
SUMMARY: Mike Pompeo tweeted support for Ron DeSantis the same night former President Donald Trump called the Florida governor "Ron DeSanctimonious" at a rally in Pennsylvania.

TITLE: Beyond George Soros, Republican mega-donors represent 7 of top 10 individuals pouring into $17B midterms
SUMMARY: Seven of the top 10 individual donors in the 2022 midterms threw massive support to Republican candidates, while the estimated total cost of state and federal races nears $17 billion.
